      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "This line of argument typically asserts that focusing on racial or group metrics implies that inherent, unchangeable group traits dictate potential or performance capacity. They would argue that any perceived differences in outcomes are attributable to innate, uncorrected biological or cognitive differences, rather than systemic barriers, thereby suggesting that forcing diversity numerically lowers overall talent quality. From this perspective, true excellence, they maintain, can only be achieved when selection is based purely on objective, individual performance metrics, irrespective of background.",
